awing <b>(e)</b> and ERCP image <b>(f )</b> show a choledochocele, or type III choledochal cyst (arrow in <b>f</b> ).<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.263055164&amp;id=F16F">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="F17A" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.263055164/asset/images/g06ma15c17a.jpeg" height="1280" width="1224" aria-labelledby="F17A" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><b>Figure 17a.</b>  <b>(a, b)</b> Drawing <b>(a)</b> and coronal MR cholangiopancreatogram <b>(b)</b> show type IV choledochal cysts. <b>(c, d)</b> Drawing <b>(c)</b> and ERCP image <b>(d)</b> show a type V choledochal cyst (Caroli disease). <b>(e)</b> Caroli disease. Contrast-enhanced T1-weighted MR image shows saccular dilatation of the IBD and the “central dot sign” (arrow).<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.263055164&amp;id=F17A">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="F17B" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.263055164/asset/images/g06ma15g17b.jpeg" height="1212" width="1280" aria-labelledby="F17B" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><b>Figure 17b.</b>  <b>(a, b)</b> Drawing <b>(a)</b> and coronal MR cholangiopancreatogram <b>(b)</b> show type IV choledochal cysts. <b>(c, d)</b> Drawing <b>(c)</b> and ERCP image <b>(d)</b> show a type V choledochal cyst (Caroli disease). <b>(e)</b> Caroli disease. Contrast-enhanced T1-weighted MR image shows saccular dilatation of the IBD and the “central dot sign” (arrow).<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.263055164&amp;id=F17B">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="F17C" clas